==English==

===Etymology===
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[ἄνθρωπος]]''' (''anthropos'') "man, mankind, [[human]], humanity" + '''[[λόγος]]''' see "[[logos]]". (''[[ἄνθρωπος]]="manfaced", from '''[[ανήρ]]''' (aner) "man" + '''[[ώπς]]''' (ops) "the eye, the face, countenance"'').

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# the [[holistic]] scientific and social study of [[humanity]]

====Derived terms====
* [[anthropologic]], or [[anthropological]]
* [[anthropologist]]
* [[cultural anthropology]]
* [[paleoanthropology]]

